  "body": "# Bug Report\n\n## Problem\n\nThe \"back gesture\" on Android doesn't close the `Send transaction` popup, but it does have effect on the app, so it can cause the app to go into background if done 2-3 times while the popup is out. After the app goes into the background and you focus it again the popup is gone and can't be opened again.\n\n#### Expected behavior\n\n* The back button exits the `Send transaction` popup\n* The popup can be opened again after app goes into background\n\n### Reproduction\n\n* Go into wallet view\n* Open the `Send transaction` popup using the blue button at the bottom\n* Try exiting it by clicking on the darkened area beyond it\n* Try exiting it by using the Android back gesture\n* Repeat the gesture few times until app goes into background\n* Re-focus the Status app\n* Try opening the `Send transaction` popup\n* See that the button does nothing now\n\nI assume the popup is still open but not visible.\n\n### Video\n\n![ezgif-2-96c3783e0caa](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2212681/77070411-77b78100-69ea-11ea-8adc-62a2dd227de6.gif)",
